Method Detail

execute

public void execute(MIDIInputPort port,
                    MIDIEndpoint srcEndPoint,
                    MIDIPacketList list)
Callback function through which a client receives MIDI messages. A MIDIReadProc function pointer is passed to the MIDIInputPortCreate and MIDIDestinationCreate functions. The client-side framework will create a high-priority receive thread on your client's behalf, and from that thread, your MIDIReadProc will be called when incoming MIDI messages arrive. Because this function is called from a separate thread, be aware of the synchronization issues when accessing data in this callback.

Parameters:
port - the MIDInputPort that contained the end point that sent this message or null if the MIDIReadProc is attached to a virtual destination
srcEndPoint - this is the end point that sent this MIDI message
list - The incoming MIDI message(s).
Throws:
If - any error occurs this method should throw an exception with the appropriate error number
